svg.desc: The chart shows obesity prevalence among adults by age group and gender in 1999 and 2013. In all five age groups, the proportion of men and women with a BMI of 30 or above was higher in 2013 than in 1999. The obesity risk increases with age. The proportion of men and women with a BMI of 30 or above is thus largest among those aged 55 to 64. 24 percent of men and 19 percent of women in this age bracket were considered obese in 2013. In all age groups, the risk of obesity is higher for men than for women.

div.p:
Source: German Federal Statistical Office, Microcensus, own calculations.
